  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-19
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Identifying the current thread
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface to identify the thread that is currently executing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-20
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Waiting for a thread to terminate
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface for a thread to wait until another thread has terminated, subject to a specified timeout.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-21
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Querying a thread state
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface to obtain a human-readable representation of a thread's current state.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-22
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Single-thread operation
STATEMENT: >>>
Where multithreading is disabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall execute the application as a single thread of control.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-23
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Thread-local storage
STATEMENT: >>>
Where thread-local storage is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall give each thread its own instance of variables declared as thread-local.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-24
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Allocating a thread stack at run time
STATEMENT: >>>
Where dynamic threads are enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a mechanism to allocate a thread stack at run time.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-25
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Releasing a run-time allocated thread stack
STATEMENT: >>>
Where dynamic threads are enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a mechanism to release a thread stack that was allocated at run time.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-26
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Iterating over threads
STATEMENT: >>>
Where thread monitoring is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a mechanism to iterate over all threads in the system, invoking a caller-supplied function for each thread.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-27
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Querying thread stack usage
STATEMENT: >>>
Where thread stack information is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a mechanism to determine the amount of stack space a thread has used.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-28
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Thread runtime statistics
STATEMENT: >>>
Where thread runtime statistics are enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a mechanism to query per-thread runtime usage statistics.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-29
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Total system runtime statistics
STATEMENT: >>>
Where thread runtime statistics are enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a mechanism to query the total runtime usage statistics across all threads.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-30
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Runtime stack safety monitoring
STATEMENT: >>>
Where thread runtime stack safety is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a mechanism to check at run time whether a thread's unused stack space has fallen below a configured threshold.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-31
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Main thread
STATEMENT: >>>
Where multithreading is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a main thread that executes the application entry point after system initialization.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-32
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Idle thread
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an idle thread that executes when no other thread is ready to run.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-33
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Querying a thread's pending timeout
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface to query the time remaining until, and the absolute system tick of, a thread's pending timeout.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-1-34
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Threads
TITLE: Enabling and disabling thread runtime statistics
STATEMENT: >>>
Where thread runtime statistics are enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide a mechanism to enable and disable runtime statistics collection for an individual thread and for the system as a whole.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16
